Since this committee was created, our mission has been to craft bipartisan solutions to make Congress work better for the people we serve.

Chair @RepDerekKilmer & I are ready to hit the ground running in 2020 to turn our 45 bipartisan recommendations into results.

Today @ModernizeCmte passed new recommendations to make Congress work better for the American ppl. 🇺🇸

The recommendations:

✅Boost civility & bipartisanship in the House 
✅Save taxpayer $
✅Increase the quality of constituent communication.

Tmrw @ModernizeCmte will vote on recommendations to boost civility & encourage bipartisanship throughout the House. After this disappointing display of extreme partisanship I am hopeful that we can move fwd from this & focus on issues that affect the everyday lives of Americans.

This partisan process has only pushed Congress & our country further down a path of division. I am disappointed in this unnecessary outcome. Our country and our President deserve better. We were elected to work together, not to tear each other down.

Tonight I voted against both articles of impeachment. In 2016, the American people voted to elect Donald Trump the President of the United States. But, for the last 3 yrs, politicians in Washington have been working to overturn the will of voters.
These bills also give our nation’s military a 3.1% pay raise & will help keep Americans safe by increasing funding for our federal law enforcement to address violent crime & drug trafficking.

#GA first priorities include secured funding for continued work on the Savannah Harbor Expansion Project & increased access to pro-bono legal services for underserved & low-income veterans in our state.
Today, I supported 2 critical gov't funding bills that support @POTUS border wall, repeal Obamacare-era taxes, & provide key resources for our military.
